Offset uniform dark-matter zoom example.

This example is identical to UniformDMGravity except the high-resolution
particle region is shifted by +1/4 of the box along each axis (from the box
centre to [0.75, 0.75, 0.75]).

The setup keeps the zoom region fully away from periodic boundaries, so no
high-resolution particles straddle box edges in the IC file.

Run with the --zoom runtime option.
